getPosition

public int getPosition()
The current byte index position of this FileStream. You may set the position programmatically. If it is set to < 0, the position will be 0. If it is set to < File.getFileSize(), the position will be File.getFileSize().

Returns:
the current position of the read pointer in this stream

setPosition

public void setPosition(int position)
Sets the position of the read pointer to a specific place in the stream

If it is set to < 0, the position will be 0. If it is set to < File.getFileSize(), the position will be File.getFileSize().

Parameters:
position - the new position of the read pointer

getBytesAvailable

public int getBytesAvailable()
Number of of bytes available from the current position to the end of the FileStream. The value of this property is effectively fileSize - position.

Returns:
number of bytes available to be read from the current position

isEof

public boolean isEof()
Tests whether the end of the FileStream has been reached. If the FileStream is unreadable, this property is true.

Returns:
true if the end of the stream has been reached

setEncoding

public void setEncoding(java.lang.String encoding)

This property defaults to UTF-8. Change it to override the default encoding used when writing to the FileStream. This can be overriden on a case-by-case basis by supplying the charset argument to the various methods which write characters.

Parameters:
encoding -

setNewLine

public void setNewLine(java.lang.String character)
Newline character used for this particular FileStream. This is the same as getSystemNewLine() when the FileStream is created. This can be set to override the default character used for splitting lines when calling readLine(String) or writeLine(String).

read

public java.lang.String read(int length)
                      throws IOException
Read a number of characters from the FileStream.

This function will read length number of characters from the stream.

If there are less than length characters left in the file, only the remaining characters in the file are read, and isEof() will be true.

If isEof() is true when this method is called, null will be returned.

The resulting String is encoded with the charset in the FileStream.getEncoding() property.

Parameters:
length - Number of characters to read.
Returns:
A String of characters, or null if there are no more characters left in the File.
Throws:
IOException - If it is not possible to read from the stream.

Read a number of characters from the FileStream.

This function will read length number of characters from the stream.

readLine

public java.lang.String readLine(java.lang.String charset)
                          throws IOException
Read a line of characters from the FileStream

This functions will read all characters up to and including the next newline in the FileStream as defined by the getNewLine() property. If there are no newlines left in the stream, the resulting string will not have a newline character and the eof property is set to true.

If eof is true when this method is called, null is returned.

The resulting String is encoded with the charset in the FileStream.encoding property

Returns:
{String} A String of characters, or null if there are no data to read.
Throws:
IOException - If it is not possible to read from the stream.

readBase64

public java.lang.String readBase64(int length)
                            throws IOException
Read bytes from the FileStream and encode it as Base64

This method will read length number of bytes from the FileStream and return the data as a Base64 encoded String.

This is typically used to encode data from binary files in order to transfer them for example over XMLHttpRequest.

As the method will read a number of bytes as specified in the length argument, and then encode it, a call to stream.readBase64(100) will not necessarily end up as a String with a length of 100.

If there are less than length bytes left in the file, only the remaining bytes in the file are read, and the eof property is set to true.

If eof is true when this method is called, null will be returned.

Parameters:
length - Number of bytes to read.
Returns:
The content of the FileStream as a Base64 encoded String, or null if there are no data to read.
Throws:
IOException - If it is not possible to read from the stream.
